'''我是罗马公民'''（{{lang|la|'''civis romanus sum'''}}{{lang|la|''cīvis rōmānus sum''}}，{{IPA-la|ˈkiːwɪs roːˈmaːnʊs ˈsʊm|classical}}，意为）是[[西塞罗|西塞罗]]《反对维勒斯的演讲》（In Verrem）中用来为[[罗马公民|罗马公民]]法律权利抗辩的短语。<ref>{{cite web|last=Cicero|first=Marcus Tullius|title=''In Verrem''|url=http://perseus.uchicago.edu/perseus-cgi/citequery3.pl?dbname=PerseusLatinTexts&query=Cic.%20Ver.%202.5.162&getid=0|work=Latin Texts and Translations|accessdate=8 April 2014|authorlink=Cicero|language=en, la|quote=...except these words, 'I am a citizen of Rome.' He fancied that by this one statement of his citizenship he could ward off all blows.|archive-date=2014-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408214056/http://perseus.uchicago.edu/perseus-cgi/citequery3.pl?dbname=PerseusLatinTexts&query=Cic.%20Ver.%202.5.162&getid=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在[[新約聖經|新約聖經]]中，[[圣保禄|圣保禄]]被囚禁和审判的时候在[[凯撒_(头衔)|凯撒]]面前宣示他作为罗马公民的权利，并且司法程序不得不暂停，直到他被带到罗马。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2022 |title=Acts 22 |accessdate=2014-08-31 |archive-date=2014-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009083737/https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2022 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2027&version=NIV |title=Acts 27 |accessdate=2014-08-31 |archive-date=2015-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108205203/https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2027&version=NIV |dead-url=no }}</ref>

这句[[修辞格|习语]]被[[第三代巴麦尊子爵亨利·坦普尔|巴麦尊勋爵]][[q:en:Henry_Temple,_3rd_Viscount_Palmerston|引用]]在他对决定在{{link-en|唐·帕西菲科事件|Don Pacifico Affair}}中封锁[[希腊|希腊]]的解释时候。在1850年6月25日于国会大厦的演讲中他宣称世界上的每一位[[英籍人士|英籍人士]]应该受到[[大英帝国|大英帝国]]的保护，就像[[罗马帝国|罗马帝国]]里的罗马公民一样。<ref name="Wawro">{{cite book|last=Wawro|first=Geoffrey|title=Warfare and Society in Europe 1792–1914|publisher=Routledge|date=2002|pages=37–38}}</ref><ref name="Muriel">{{cite book|last=Chamberlain|first=Muriel Evelyn|title=British foreign policy in the age of Palmerston|publisher=Longman|date=1980|series=Seminar studies in history|page=125}}</ref>
</blockquote>

